('fdf24098-e39c-53e2-8b78-55b8aae53cbf', '02713a3e-ded7-4f5d-8e3c-ff77f8e796b6', 91, 'Senior RPLS Timothy Albert Lenz (license #4393, granted 1986); est. age ~70 (license_tenure_proxy assuming typical RPLS-earn age of 30 — TX RPLS requires 4yr college + 4yr supervised survey-in-training + state exam); firm tenure 40yr. Second RPLS Lemuel Theodore Sinclair (granted 1995, est. age ~61).', 75, '40yr-tenured firm with 3 active RPLS — TX RPLS license is a 4yr-college + 4yr-apprentice + exam-gated skilled-trade moat; firm passes the >5yr in-business hard gate; vertical has documented recurring B2B from oil/gas ROW + construction stake-out + ALTA + FEMA elev certs. Default L2 mid-range pending enrichment-time confirmation of staff count + recurring program mix (homebuilder logos / MSA language).', 45, 'Long tenure (40yr) suggests classic exit-window — owner is operationally entrenched but at natural retirement age. (Default scoring — confirm individual coasting tells at enrichment-time live-fetch.)', 68, 'San Antonio metro (San Antonio, Bexar County) — steady boundary + civil-engineering subcontract market. LOW-PE-ATTENTION vertical: only Bowman (NASDAQ:BWMN) + Westwood (Endeavour Capital) are PE-backed rollup platforms in TX; large-AEC strategics (Stantec, WSP, AECOM, Kimley-Horn, Cobb Fendley, LJA) only bolt-on $5M+ rev firms — sub-$5M independents are structurally under-targeted. ETA/search-fund appetite emerging fast 2024-2026 (top-15 vertical in Stanford Search Fund Study). +2 baseline boost for solo/2-RPLS metros = opportunity zone.', 70, 'B_forward', 'Senior RPLS Timothy Albert Lenz (granted 1986, est. age ~70 via license_tenure_proxy, 40yr firm tenure); SINCLAIR LAND SURVEYING, INC. in San Antonio, Bexar County. 3-RPLS firm. L1 91 / L2 75 / L3 45 / L4 68 → final 70, tier B_forward. LOW-PE-ATTENTION vertical: only Bowman + Westwood active in TX surveying-firm PE rollup; sub-$5M independent universe is structurally under-targeted. Forward to ETA/search-fund community.', 'AI / ops modernization play on a 40yr-tenured single-RPLS surveying firm in San Antonio:  (1) drone/UAV survey program (~25-40% labor savings on topo + as-built); (2) 3D laser scanning + reality capture for as-built and infrastructure work; (3) online project portal for ALTA / FEMA / boundary client self-service; (4) RTK GPS base station network for sub-cm field productivity; (5) automated CAD/drafting workflow + AI plat-review. Plausible 1.5-2× EBITDA path 18-24 months. Off-market multiple 3-5× EBITDA in current LOW-PE-attention environment; would shift to 5-7× as ETA/search-fund deal-velocity ramps 2026-2027.', 'low', 0.45),
